{
  "stem": "19198.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, there was-- [LAUGHS] --nobody that was anybody in the United States that Stephen Wise didn't know or that didn't know Stephen Wise.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Steven Wise could pick up a phone and call just about anybody in the United States, from the-- from the president down to everybody else.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the-- the question of-- of 'little' and 'much,' I think, is a very subjective judgment.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Certainly, for those of us who-- who were saved, everything that needed to be done was done.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was under the impression that, certainly for German Jewry, who were the first to be impacted by the Nazis, a great deal was done.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As far as the-- the crucial problem affecting the mass of-- of Jewry in Eastern Europe, the circumstances had changed to the-- to the point where everything worked against the Jews, both those who were immediately hit by the-- by the Nazis and also for those who had-- who wanted to help.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because you had a-- a-- a country that, at that time, was winning a war making a priority of destroying the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the-- until the Allies were in a position where they could really hurt Germany, which was not until late in the war, governments could do very little to help the Jews.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Yes, they could have bombed the-- the rails to Auschwitz and didn't do that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "How much that would have helped is also questionable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because if they didn't kill in Auschwitz, they would have killed someplace else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was really very little they could do, short of winning the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When did I--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1946.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
